TY  - JOUR
T1  - Testing for Asymmetric Information in Insurance Markets
AU  - Chiappori, Pierre‐Andre
AU  - Salanie, Bernard
Y1  - 2000/02/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/262111
DO  - 10.1086/262111
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 56
EP  - 78
VL  - 108
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - The first goal of this paper is to provide a simple and general test of the presence of asymmetric information in contractual relationships within a competitive context. We also argue that insurance data are particularly well suited to such empirical investigations. To illustrate this claim, we use data on contracts and accidents to investigate the extent of asymmetric information in the French market for automobile insurance. Using various parametric and nonparametric methods, we find no evidence for the presence of asymmetric information in this market.
AB  - The first goal of this paper is to provide a simple and general test of the presence of asymmetric information in contractual relationships within a competitive context. We also argue that insurance data are particularly well suited to such empirical investigations. To illustrate this claim, we use data on contracts and accidents to investigate the extent of asymmetric information in the French market for automobile insurance. Using various parametric and nonparametric methods, we find no evidence for the presence of asymmetric information in this market.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/262111
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/262111
Y2  - 2024/03/19
